<!-- ── Page Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container page-hero-inner">
    <span class="section-eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p>Last updated: <strong>{{lastUpdated}}</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Terms Content ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section--sm section">
  <div class="container policy-container">

    <div class="callout callout--info" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-10);">
      <span>📋</span>
      <span>
        <strong>The short version:</strong> Use Soren to organize events in your Discord community.
        Don't use it to harm others, break Discord's rules, or do anything illegal. Be respectful.
        That's really all there is to it.
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Acceptance -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By adding Soren to your Discord server or using any of its slash commands, buttons, or
        features, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, please
        remove Soren from your server and discontinue use.
      </p>
      <p>
        These Terms apply to all users of Soren, including server administrators, event creators,
        and regular members who interact with RSVP buttons.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 2. Description of Service -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        Soren is a Discord bot that provides calendar and event management functionality for
        Discord communities. Its features include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Creating and managing events with RSVP signups via slash commands</li>
        <li>Sending configurable pre-event reminders</li>
        <li>Supporting recurring events on various schedules</li>
        <li>Optional integration with Google Calendar</li>
        <li>A Premium tier with expanded limits, available as a one-time purchase</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Soren is a third-party bot and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by
        Discord Inc. in any way. Use of Soren is subject to
        <a href="https://discord.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord's Terms of Service</a>
        in addition to these terms.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 3. Eligibility -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
      <p>To use Soren, you must:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Be at least 13 years of age (as required by Discord's Terms of Service)</li>
        <li>Have a valid Discord account in good standing</li>
        <li>Have the appropriate permissions in your Discord server to add bots (for server administrators)</li>
        <li>Comply with all applicable local, provincial, national, and international laws</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- 4. Acceptable Use -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree to use Soren only for its intended purpose of community event management. You agree <strong>not</strong> to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use Soren to harass, threaten, harm, or discriminate against any individual or group</li>
        <li>Create events with content that is illegal, defamatory, obscene, or violates any third-party rights</li>
        <li>Attempt to exploit, abuse, or circumvent any limitations or security measures in Soren</li>
        <li>Use Soren to spam Discord channels with excessive event embeds or reminder messages</li>
        <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or extract proprietary logic from Soren (note: the source code is already publicly available on GitHub)</li>
        <li>Resell, sublicense, or misrepresent Soren as your own product</li>
        <li>Use Soren in any way that violates Discord's <a href="https://discord.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Terms of Service</a> or <a href="https://discord.com/guidelines" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Community Guidelines</a></li>
        <li>Attempt to interfere with the bot's normal operation or the experience of other users</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- 5. Premium Tier -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. Premium Tier</h2>
      <p>
        Soren offers an optional Premium tier for a <strong>one-time fee of {{premiumPrice}} per server</strong>.
        Premium is activated by redeeming a unique code via the <code>/premiumcode</code> command.
      </p>

      <h3>What Premium includes</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Up to 50 active events per server (vs. 10 on the free tier)</li>
        <li>Up to 100 RSVP names shown per event (vs. 50 on the free tier)</li>
        <li>10 embed color options (vs. 3 on the free tier)</li>
        <li>Up to 5 Google Calendar integrations (vs. 2 on the free tier)</li>
        <li>Access to all future premium features as they are released</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Premium terms</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Premium is <strong>per server</strong> — each server that wants Premium requires its own purchase and activation code.</li>
        <li>Premium codes are <strong>single-use</strong> — once redeemed by a server, the code cannot be used again.</li>
        <li>Premium is <strong>non-transferable</strong> between servers.</li>
        <li>We do not offer refunds on Premium purchases once a code has been redeemed and activated.</li>
        <li>If Soren is removed from a server and re-added, the Premium status associated with that server ID is retained in our database and will be restored.</li>
        <li>We reserve the right to revoke Premium access from servers found to be in violation of these Terms of Service without refund.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout callout--info" style="margin-top:var(--space-5);">
        <span>ℹ️</span>
        <span>
          Premium purchases are processed externally via the Soren website. We do not handle
          or store any payment card information. Payment processing is handled by our
          payment provider and is subject to their terms.
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 6. Google Calendar Integration -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. Google Calendar Integration</h2>
      <p>
        Soren's Google Calendar integration is entirely optional. By choosing to connect a
        Google Calendar, you acknowledge that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You authorize Soren to read from and write to the connected Google Calendar on your behalf</li>
        <li>You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to connect the calendar you authorize (e.g. shared team calendars)</li>
        <li>You can revoke Soren's access at any time via <code>/gcal disconnect</code>, <code>/gcalint remove</code>, or directly through your <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Account permissions</a></li>
        <li>Soren's use of Google Calendar APIs is subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Terms of Service</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

